{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015rL6bgmjKS8EbaZQjd6pyg","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect. Now let me create the final comprehensive report.\n\n## UX/COPY AUDIT REPORT: changebrief\n\n### 1. LANDING PAGE (Astro, `/landing`)\n\n#### Key Files & Structure\n- **Main pages**: `/landing/src/pages/index.astro`, `/landing/src/pages/compliance.astro`, `/landing/src/pages/sv/*.astro` (all translated)\n- **Components used**: Only `LandingPage.astro` and `CompliancePage.astro` render; Hero, Problem, Features, HowItWorks, Pricing, FAQ, UseCases are all **embedded inline** within those two components (lines 73-274 in LandingPage.astro)\n- **i18n file**: `/landing/src/i18n.ts` (lines 1-212) — all copy is centralized\n- **Swedish support**: Yes — `/sv` pages exist at `/landing/src/pages/sv/index.astro`, `/landing/src/pages/sv/compliance.astro`, `/landing/src/pages/sv/privacy.astro`, `/landing/src/pages/sv/security.astro`, `/landing/src/pages/sv/terms.astro`\n\n#### Trust-Signal Stats (Hard-coded in i18n)\n- **60+ authorities** (SE/DK/NO/FI/EU/US) — line 128, 184, 195 in i18n.ts\n- **8 sectors** — line 185\n- **5 countries** — line 186\n- **9 integrations** — line 187\n- **0 hard-coded specific numbers** in code for agencies monitored globally (these are pre-configured suggestions, not live stats)\n\n#### i18n Keys Map\n\n**Hero section** (lines 5-14):\n```\nhero.badge: \"Know what changed in plain English\" (en) / \"Vet vad som ändrades — på ren svenska\" (sv)\nhero.h1a: \"See what changed\"\nhero.h1b: \"not just that something changed\"\nhero.sub: [full description]\nhero.cta1: \"Get started free\"\nhero.cta2: \"See how it works\"\nhero.demo.text: \"Acme Corp removed the\"\nhero.demo.raised: \"button and raised the Pro price from\"\nhero.demo.to: \"to\"\n```\n\n**How it works** (lines 21-31):\n```\nhow.h2: \"How it works\"\nhow.sub: \"Three steps. No code.\"\nhow.s1/s2/s3: Step titles & descriptions\n```\n\n**Use cases** (lines 32-45):\n```\nuse.h2: \"Use cases\"\nuse.sub: \"One tool. Dozens of high-value applications.\"\nuse.comp.h/p: \"Competitor pricing\"\nuse.reg.h/p: \"Regulatory changes\"\nuse.vendor.h/p: \"SaaS terms & contracts\"\nuse.hiring.h/p: \"Hiring & strategy intel\"\nuse.ecom.h/p: \"Supplier & MAP pricing\"\nuse.site.h/p: \"Your own site integrity\"\n```\n\n**Pricing** (lines 60-79):\n```\nprice.h2: \"Simple pricing\"\nprice.sub: \"Start free. Upgrade when you need more.\"\nprice.free.desc: \"Try it at no cost.\"\nprice.pro.desc: \"25 pages, Slack notifications, 90 days of history.\"\nprice.team.desc: \"100 pages, all integrations, API access.\"\nprice.save: \"save 17%\"\nprice.pages: \"monitored pages\"\nprice.checks: \"checks/mo\"\nprice.days: \"days of history\"\n```\n\n**Features** (lines 46-59):\n```\nfeat.ai: \"AI-powered summaries\"\nfeat.score: \"Importance score (1-10)\"\nfeat.slack: \"Slack, Teams & Discord\"\nfeat.sched: \"Scheduled monitoring\"\nfeat.hist: \"Screenshot history\"\nfeat.api: \"REST API & Webhooks\"\n```\n\n**FAQ** (lines 79-87):\n```\nfaq.q1/a1: \"How is changebrief different from Visualping?\"\nfaq.q2/a2: \"How accurate are the summaries?\"\nfaq.q3/a3: \"Can I monitor pages behind a login?\"\nfaq.q4/a4: \"Where is data hosted?\"\n```\n\n**Footer** (lines 88-95):\n```\nfooter.h2a/b/c: \"Start monitoring your most important pages today\"\nfooter.sub: \"Free to get started. No credit card required.\"\nfooter.cta: \"Create account — free\"\nfooter.docs/privacy/contact: Navigation links\n```\n\n**Compliance landing** (lines 97-212): Full separate set for regulatory-focused page with 60+ authorities messaging, sector watchlists, ISO features, and compliance FAQ.\n\n---\n\n### 2. WEB APP (Next.js, `/app`)\n\n#### Root & Auth Flow\n- **`app/src/app/page.tsx`** (lines 1-10): Redirects to `/dashboard` if authenticated, `/login` otherwise. **No landing page in app.**\n- **`app/src/app/login/page.tsx`** (lines 1-67): Email prompt missing; shows \"Sign in to get started\" + Google/GitHub buttons. Two buttons **lack aria-labels or title attributes** (SVG icons). Copy at line 29 uses `t('login.title', locale)` which resolves to \"Sign in to get started\" (en) / \"Logga in för att komma igång\" (sv).\n\n**Login copy** (`app/src/lib/i18n.ts` lines 75-78):\n```\nlogin.title: \"Sign in to get started\" / \"Logga in för att komma igång\"\nlogin.google: \"Continue with Google\" / \"Fortsätt med Google\"\nlogin.github: \"Continue with GitHub\" / \"Fortsätt med GitHub\"\n```\n\n#### Dashboard Structure\n**`app/src/app/dashboard/page.tsx`** (lines 1-306): Main dashboard layout with five major sections:\n\n1. **Stats bar** (lines 136-188): Shows \"Monitored\" (pages), \"Changes (7d)\", \"Checks (7d)\", \"Last check\". If compliance data exists, separate red/amber/emerald cards show \"Action required\", \"Review\", \"Reviewed (7d)\".\n   \n2. **Activity Feed** (lines 214-250): Shows monitored URLs with changes detected, AI summaries, importance scores (1-10).\n\n3. **Compliance section** (lines 252-264): Tabbed interface with `ComplianceTabs` — displays regulatory changes with filtering by action level (action_required/review_recommended/info_only), jurisdiction tagging, document type.\n\n4. **Monitored Pages** (lines 267-286): Grid of watched URLs with inline `AddUrlForm`.\n\n5. **Discover** (lines 289-296): `PopularWatchlists` component showing one-click regulatory authorities and popular pages.\n\n**Header** (lines 78-121): Shows plan badge, upgrade button (if free/pro), feedback CTA (amber, pulsing), email, settings gear, theme toggle, language switcher.\n\n#### Compliance Components\n\n**`compliance-feed.tsx`** (lines 1-409):\n- **Empty state** (lines 144-179): Shows \"ghost preview\" of what a compliance change looks like (dashed border, opacity-50). Copy: \"This is what your regulatory changes will look like\" (en) / \"Så kommer dina regulatoriska ändringar att se ut\" (sv). **Ghost state is helpful but **static**—no CTA to add agencies.**\n- **Stats strip** (lines 187-203): Red/amber badges showing \"X need action\", \"X to review\".\n- **Filters** (lines 205-231): \"All\" / \"Action required\" / \"Review\" / \"Info\" buttons with counts; jurisdiction dropdown; export audit trail button (Pro feature).\n- **Entries** (lines 252-406): Expandable rows per change with:\n  - Timestamp (formatted `formatDate()`)\n  - Action badge (red/amber/slate with dot indicator + tooltip)\n  - SLA overdue indicator (⚠ red label if reviewed_at is null AND age > slaActionHours/slaReviewHours)\n  - Jurisdiction tag (code style)\n  - Name + summary (truncated)\n  - Importance score (1/10) colored by severity\n  - Document type label\n  - URL link\n  - Changed elements (pills)\n  - \"Mark as reviewed\" / \"Reviewed\" status with date\n  - Team plan only: assign-to input with email address field\n\n**`compliance-onboarding.tsx`** (lines 1-293):\n- **Step 1** (lines 154-174): Multi-select jurisdictions (SE, DK, NO, FI, EU, US)\n- **Step 2** (lines 178-198): Select sector (Finance, Health, Data, Transport, Environment, Labor, Laws & Government)\n- **Step 3** (lines 201-257): Shows matched authorities from `suggestions.json`, with \"Add all recommended\" button + progress bar during adding\n- **Copy issues**: No email/contact field validation; just adds by jurisdiction + sector combination\n- **No confusing CTAs** — flow is clear but **lacks explanation of what each sector monitors** before selection\n\n**`compliance-overview.tsx`**: Table view of all monitored authorities with last-change timestamp, jurisdiction, document type, action level, review status, printable.\n\n**`compliance-pdf-export.tsx`**: Pro feature for exporting audit trails.\n\n#### Add URL Form\n**`add-url-form.tsx`** (lines 81-150+):\n- **Basic fields**: URL, name, submit\n- **Advanced section** (collapsible): CSS selector, cookies (multi-row), HTTP headers (multi-row), webhook URL\n- **Copy** (`app/src/lib/i18n.ts` lines 22-38):\n  ```\n  form.placeholder.url: \"https://example.com/pricing\"\n  form.add: \"Add\" / \"Lägg till\"\n  form.success: \"Monitoring started — first check runs within the hour.\"\n  form.limit: \"You've reached your plan's limit of monitored pages.\"\n  form.advanced: \"Advanced: monitor pages behind login, target specific elements\"\n  form.selector.help: \"Only monitor a specific part of the page instead of the whole thing. Leave empty to monitor the full page.\"\n  form.cookies.help: \"For pages behind a login. Find cookies in your browser: Settings → Privacy → Cookies.\"\n  ```\n\n#### First-Time UX\n**`onboarding.tsx`** (lines 23-53):\n- **Three-step card** (centered, glass-morphic): \"Add a page to monitor\", \"We check automatically\", \"AI tells you what changed\"\n- **Only shown to new users** (no monitored URLs or history)\n- **Copy**: \"Welcome to changebrief\" / \"Välkommen till changebrief\" + \"Three steps to start monitoring web pages.\"\n- **Icons but no alt text** on SVG icons (no aria-labels)\n\n**`popular-watchlists.tsx`** (lines 58-200+):\n- Shows suggested URLs by category (Finance, Transport, Health, Data, Privacy, Environment, Labor, Laws, Pricing, Newsrooms, Standards, Status)\n- One-click add with color-coded category badges\n- Shows jurisdiction flags (SE, DK, NO, FI, EU, US)\n- **Empty state**: None — always shows suggestions\n\n#### Empty States & Edge Cases\n1. **No monitored pages** → `Onboarding` or `ComplianceOnboarding` shown\n2. **No activity yet** → Activity feed shows: \"No changes detected yet. Pages are checked every 6 hours. Changes will appear here automatically.\"\n3. **Pending first check** (lines 190-212): Blue banner with spinner + message: \"Waiting for first check. {N} page(s) will be checked within 6 hours. We'll email you when results are ready.\"\n4. **Compliance with no changes** (lines 144-179 in compliance-feed.tsx): Ghost preview shown with \"Lägg till myndigheter under Upptäck för att börja bevaka\" (sv)\n\n#### Demo Page\n**`app/src/app/demo/page.tsx`** (lines 1-247):\n- **Anonymous, read-only compliance demo** with mock data (6 regulatory changes from FI, Transportstyrelsen, EU DORA, IMY, Riksbanken, Danish FSA)\n- **Stats**: Shows \"Action required\", \"Review\", \"Reviewed (7d)\", \"Last check\", \"Pages monitored\", \"Changes (7d)\", \"Total checks (7d)\"\n- **Banner at top**: \"This is an interactive demo with sample data. Sign up free to monitor your own regulatory sources.\"\n- **All buttons disabled/opacity-60** on \"Mark reviewed\" (line 191-195)\n- **No edit/delete actions** — purely demonstrative\n- **CTA at bottom**: Two links to `/login` and `/` (Learn more)\n\n---\n\n### 3. DATA & CONSTANTS\n\n#### Regulatory Sources (Pre-configured)\n**`app/src/data/suggestions.json`** (sample, lines 1-50):\n```json\nTransportstyrelsen – New rules (SE) [Transport & Infrastructure]\nTrafikverket – Regulations (SE) [Transport & Infrastructure]\nJordbruksverket – Regulations (SE) [Transport & Infrastructure]\nHaV – Maritime regulations (SE) [Transport & Infrastructure]\nFinansinspektionen – Regs (SE) [Finance & Banking]\n[... 50+ more across FI, DK, NO, EU, US]\n```\nEach entry has: url, name (en), name_sv (sv), category, description (en), description_sv (sv), jurisdiction.\n\n#### Database Schema\n**`shared/schema.ts`** (lines 1-110):\n\n**Users table**:\n```sql\nid (TEXT PK), email (TEXT UNIQUE), name, image, plan ('free'|'pro'|'team'), \npolar_customer_id, notify_email (INT), slack_webhook_url, \nnotify_action_required (INT), notify_review_recommended (INT), notify_info_only (INT),\nwebhook_url, teams_webhook_url, discord_webhook_url, pagerduty_routing_key,\nsla_action_hours (INT, default 48), sla_review_hours (INT, default 168),\ndigest_frequency ('weekly'|'daily'), locale ('en'|'sv'),\ncreated_at\n```\n\n**Watched_urls table**:\n```sql\nid (INT PK), user_id, url, name, active (INT), threshold (REAL, 0.3 default),\nselector, mobile (INT), min_importance (INT, 5 default