tinue with GitHub\" / \"Fortsätt med GitHub\"\n```\n\n#### Dashboard Structure\n**`app/src/app/dashboard/page.tsx`** (lines 1-306): Main dashboard layout with five major sections:\n\n1. **Stats bar** (lines 136-188): Shows \"Monitored\" (pages), \"Changes (7d)\", \"Checks (7d)\", \"Last check\". If compliance data exists, separate red/amber/emerald cards show \"Action required\", \"Review\", \"Reviewed (7d)\".\n   \n2. **Activity Feed** (lines 214-250): Shows monitored URLs with changes detected, AI summaries, importance scores (1-10).\n\n3. **Compliance section** (lines 252-264): Tabbed interface with `ComplianceTabs` — displays regulatory changes with filtering by action level (action_required/review_recommended/info_only), jurisdiction tagging, document type.\n\n4. **Monitored Pages** (lines 267-286): Grid of watched URLs with inline `AddUrlForm`.\n\n5. **Discover** (lines 289-296): `PopularWatchlists` component showing one-click regulatory authorities and popular pages.\n\n**Header** (lines 78-121): Shows plan badge, upgrade button (if free/pro), feedback CTA (amber, pulsing), email, settings gear, theme toggle, language switcher.\n\n#### Compliance Components\n\n**`compliance-feed.tsx`** (lines 1-409):\n- **Empty state** (lines 144-179): Shows \"ghost preview\" of what a compliance change looks like (dashed border, opacity-50). Copy: \"This is what your regulatory changes will look like\" (en) / \"Så kommer dina regulatoriska ändringar att se ut\" (sv). **Ghost state is helpful but **static**—no CTA to add agencies.**\n- **Stats strip** (lines 187-203): Red/amber badges showing \"X need action\", \"X to review\".\n- **Filters** (lines 205-231): \"All\" / \"Action required\" / \"Review\" / \"Info\" buttons with counts; jurisdiction dropdown; export audit trail button (Pro feature).\n- **Entries** (lines 252-406): Expandable rows per change with:\n  - Timestamp (formatted `formatDate()`)\n  - Action badge (red/amber/slate with dot indicator + tooltip)\n  - SLA ov